verbose_text: With FAK inhibition for 2 h, the expression level of RhoA decreased in both endothelial and hepatoblastoma cells at 5-10 min, but had increased at 2 h (XREF_FIG), which is consistent with previous results, indicating that inhibition of FAK induced the retraction of lamellipodia at the cell protrusions and the formation of filamentous stress fibers in the cell body (XREF_FIG).
